Package: operantlunar
Title: Differentiating Reward Maximization from Melioration via Operant Conditioning
Version: 0.4.1
Authors@R: person("Sondre", "Skarsten", email = "sondreskarsten@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Sondre Skarsten [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Sondre Skarsten <sondreskarsten@gmail.com>
Description: A tabular reinforcement-learning instrument that mechanistically
    differentiates reward-maximizing control (the law of effect) from descriptive
    melioration (the matching law). Provides a shared learning skeleton; a library
    of learning rules (Q-learning, SARSA, expected SARSA, double Q-learning,
    actor-critic, a model-based planner, gradient-bandit and rate-tracking
    melioration, win-stay-lose-shift); a battery of operant paradigms (schedule
    family, melioration trap, extinction, probability matching, self-control /
    delay discounting, differential reinforcement of low rates, progressive ratio,
    risk sensitivity, reinforcer devaluation, changeover-delay concurrent
    schedules); an analysis layer with generalized-matching, Herrnstein-hyperbola
    and discounting fits and a differentiation-matrix capstone; hashed tile coding
    with linear function-approximation agents and a generic Gymnasium adapter; an
    optional Python LunarLander environment via reticulate; and a bundled Shiny app.
